<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-100-866  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 100 866.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Jan 29 1990 v36 n1794 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SEMI told: '90 gear sales will be flat. (electronic equipment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Winkler, Eric.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Experts predict flat sales of semiconductor equipment in 1990, andvendors say that they are scaling back their inventories.andP;  Mostindustry analysts say that 1990 will be the end of a businesscycle but not an all-out recession.andP;  Track equipment anddeposition and diffusion technologies are not expected to grow in1990, but experts forecast 26 percent growth in epitaxialthin-film deposition and rapid thermal processing in 1991.andP;  Thelithography industry is an exception to the general downturnfacing equipment makers, with a 5 percent revenue increaseforecast for 1990 and a 23 percent increase the following year.andO;Important technologies driving the equipment market will beelectron cyclotron resonance and electron-beam devices.andO;Commercial communications will be a growth market, and Japan willremain an area of heated competition.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Semiconductor industrySalesSemiconductor Production EquipmentTest EquipmentCircuit Design.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>